  "response": "I don't have personal experiences or preferences, but I can share some of the most popular and influential songs from 2016 that many people enjoyed:\n\n1. **\"Closer\" by The Chainsmokers ft. Halsey** \u2013 This song became a massive hit worldwide and topped charts in multiple countries.\n2. **\"One Dance\" by Drake ft. Wizkid and Kyla** \u2013 Known for its catchy melody and dancehall influence, it was a global favorite.\n3. **\"Can't Stop the Feeling!\" by Justin Timberlake** \u2013 An upbeat track that became synonymous with feel-good vibes and was featured in the animated film *Trolls*.\n4. **\"Cheap Thrills\" by Sia ft. Sean Paul** \u2013 A danceable anthem that showcased Sia's distinctive vocal style.\n5. **\"Work\" by Rihanna ft. Drake** \u2013 This song blended dancehall and pop elements, becoming a staple in clubs and on radio stations.\n\nIf you're looking for recommendations or more information about music from 2016, feel free to ask!",
